honetic wordplay are estranged and heard anew. The Ways of the Word fluidly and intuitively reveals a verbal alchemy that is as riveting as it is elusive and mysterious.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aAmerican literaturey19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aAmerican literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish languagexStyle. 0aEnglish literaturey19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aWord (Linguistics) 0aWord (Linguistics). 4aFilm. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aPerforming Arts & Drama. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Semiotics & Theory.2bisacsh  aStylistic analysis, word play, Victorian fiction, immersive reading, surface reading, symptomatic reading, Richard Powers.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073908408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311075182640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150176142340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501761423423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501761423/original  a978-3-11-073908-4  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075182-6  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK